Davy McKee Ltd, a subsidiary of U.K.Engineering and contruction company Davy Corp Plc, has beenawarded a contract worth around 15 mln stg for the design of azinc and lead smelter in India, a spokesman for the companysaid.    The contract is being funded by Britain's OverseasDevelopment Administration as part of a total grant of 73.65mln stg to India's state-owned Hindustan Zinc Ltd.    The grant is for the development of a major zinc and leadmine and associated smelting complex in Rajastan, North WestIndia, the agency said.    The agency said the project was expected to account for 44pct of India's total production of zinc.    A total 55 mln stg of the grant is allocated for the supplyof goods and services from Britain. The grant comes as part ofpackage announced on March 13 for Indian mineral development.    The agency is also paying a further 31 mln stg to India'scoal sector, for the expansion of its indigenous coaldevelopment programme, using British-designed longwalltechnology. Reuter&#3;